# Auto Git Push Rule

## Overview
This rule ensures that any file changes in the AppSamurai Dashboard project are automatically committed and pushed to GitHub.

## Automatic Git Workflow
When files are modified, the following Git commands will be executed automatically:

1. **Stage Changes**: `git add .`
2. **Commit Changes**: `git commit -m "Auto-commit: [description of changes]"`
3. **Push to GitHub**: `git push origin main`

## Implementation Pattern
```bash
# Automatic staging
git add .

# Smart commit message generation
git commit -m "Auto-commit: $(date +%Y-%m-%d_%H:%M:%S) - $(git status --porcelain | head -1 | cut -c4-)"

# Push to remote
git push origin main
```

## File Monitoring
This rule applies to all project files except:
- `node_modules/`
- `dist/`
- `.git/`
- `.DS_Store`
- `*.log`

## Commit Message Format
Auto-generated commit messages follow this pattern:
- `Auto-commit: YYYY-MM-DD_HH:MM:SS - [file description]`
- Example: `Auto-commit: 2025-01-03_16:30:45 - Updated Dashboard component`

## Error Handling
If push fails due to conflicts:
1. Pull latest changes: `git pull origin main`
2. Resolve conflicts if any
3. Re-push: `git push origin main`

## GitHub Integration
- Repository: https://github.com/BeratGocer/appsamurai-dashboard
- Branch: main
- Remote: origin

## Usage Instructions
1. Make changes to any project file
2. Save the file
3. Rule automatically detects changes
4. Git commands execute automatically
5. Changes are pushed to GitHub

## Safety Measures
- Only staged files are committed
- Commit messages include timestamp
- Push only to main branch
- No force push operations
- Preserves existing Git history